Janne wrote:Oooh, how could I forget: Indiana Jones and The Raiders of The Lost Ark.Incidentally: the original end to that film is the meeting with the govt. folks followed by the shot of the huge warehouse. If it hadn't been for Marcia Lucas (film editor, occasional screenwriter and wife of George), there would never have been the scene that goes between those two shots, where Indy meets Marion outside the building, and we'd all be posting to this day about how nonsensical it is that Indy goes through the whole film trying to be with her and/or rescue her and then she disappears with no explanation.Just one example of the many ways in which Marcia Lucas rescued a dumb moment and helped it to be great.
hux
