Jakal wrote:nastro wrote:Yes, I always liked the 'Deckard is a replicant' idea.It's not just an idea. It's the established ending to the film. Ridley explicitly said so himself. Deckard is a replicant.Yep. However, my sole complaint about the later cuts of Blade Runner (I don't think it was in the theatrical release) is the split-second shot of Deckard with glowing eyes. It messes up the film in two ways:1) Because you see Rachael with glowing eyes earlier, now you know Deckard is a replicant. The film works so much better if you're not sure, but you just assume he is from the not-that-subtle connection between his dream and Gaff's parting origami gift.2) It totally contradicts the whole, "It's so hard to tell a replicant from a human that we developed the Voight-Kampff test to help us do it", thing. It makes you think, 'Well, just look for the glowing eyes, you idiots! Job done.'
