andyfatbastard wrote:Frennzy wrote:TwinIon wrote:I'm not sure how I haven't seen There Will Be Blood mentioned, or did I miss it? I almost stood up in the theater an cheered at that ending.I loved everything about that movie except the ending. WTF? They don't even show it. You spend 2+ hours of your life following this guy, rooting for him, and then...bam. You see the aftermath of...what...exactly? And then bad guy? What was the scene all about?It turns out he was the bad guy all along. He was just better at hiding it when he was younger, because becoming successful - thus proving he was better than everyone else - was the most important thing to him. Once he had done that, he was free to be as horrible a cunt as he liked - which he did with just as much fervour and cut-throat delight as he did in becoming successful.If you want to look at it from a symbolic level too, it's the winning of capitalism (unfettered, at that) over religious fundamentalism in early 20th century America, for good or bad. Neither of the two is represented as having a steady moral compass, and the ham-fisted execution of this debate, as far as the movie goes, lacks any real finesse or nuance.
